==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elæis
<hw>E*l⟦ae⟧"is</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ olive tree.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
palms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>El⟦ae⟧is Guineensis</xex>, the African oil palm, is
a tree twenty or thirty feet high, with immense pinnate leaves and large
masses of fruit. The berries are rather larger than olives, and when
boiled in water yield the orange-red palm oil.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elaeolite</ent>⟦br⟧
